[SN]TITLE[SN]
British and Irish Lions: Johnny Sexton and Sean O'Brien fitness boost

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The British and Irish Lions have been boosted by the news that Johnny Sexton took a full part in squad training on Thursday and Sean O'Brien is on the verge of a return to full fitness.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fly-half Sexton trained in Kildare after having a head injury assessment (HIA) following Leinster's Pro12 semi-final defeat by Scarlets.
Flanker O'Brien missed that match because of a "tightness in his calf".
O'Brien has done some running but has yet to return to full training.
